# Bahrain Messaging Hub Data Deletion Request

Last updated: April 29, 2026

## Account and Data Deletion

If you want to request account and data deletion, email:

- info@ncst.bh

In your request, include:

- The phone number registered on your Bahrain Messaging Hub account
- A short note that you are requesting account deletion

## Steps to Request Deletion

1. Send your request from your preferred email to `info@ncst.bh`.
2. Include the phone number linked to your Bahrain Messaging Hub account.
3. Our support team will contact you if additional identity confirmation is required.
4. After successful verification, we process your deletion request.

## Verification Process

Before deleting any data, our team will verify the identity of the user to protect account security and prevent unauthorized deletion requests.

## What Data Is Deleted

After your request is verified, we delete the account data associated with the provided phone number, including:

- Profile data (such as display name, profile photo, and status)
- Message data and supported attachments associated with the account
- App contact mapping data linked to the account
- Device push-notification tokens linked to the account

## What Data May Be Kept and Retention

Some limited records may be retained for legal, security, fraud-prevention, or compliance purposes.

- If retention is required, such records are kept only for the required period and then deleted.
- Operational backup copies may take additional time to expire from backup systems.

## Contact

For deletion requests and follow-up, contact:

